paragraph.def:
“contract of carriage” (運輸合約) means a contract made by or on behalf of a carrier for the
                carriage by sea of a passenger or of a passenger and his luggage, as the case may
                be;

“ship” (船、船舶) means only a seagoing vessel,
                excluding an air-cushion
                vehicle;

subsection.content:
claims in respect of other loss resulting from infringement of rights other
                    than contractual rights, occurring in direct connection with the operation of
                    the ship or salvage operations;

claims in respect of the raising, removal, destruction or the rendering
                    harmless of a ship which is sunk, wrecked, stranded or abandoned, including
                    anything that is or has been on board such ship;

claims for oil pollution damage within the meaning of the International
                    Convention on Civil Liability for Oil Pollution Damage dated 29 November 1969 or
                    of any amendment or Protocol thereto which is in force;

